\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fact:sufbasictop"

\end_inset

 since 
\begin_inset Formula $B\in\mathcal{B}^{n}$
\end_inset

 are basic sets for the topology [topological 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma$
\end_inset

-algebra is generated by basic sets in the topology]) and so finite intersection
s
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
S\left(t_{1},B_{1}\right)\cap\cdots\cap S\left(t_{k},B_{k}\right)=\left\{ \omega_{X}\in\tilde{\Omega}=\left(\mathbb{R}^{n}\right)^{T};\omega_{X}\left(t_{1}\right)\in B_{1},\dots,\omega_{X}\left(t_{k}\right)\in B_{k}\right\} 
\]

\end_inset

form a basis for the product topology on 
\begin_inset Formula $\tilde{\Omega}$
\end_inset

 and unions of those then form the actual elements of the product topology
